Rant Rhapsody
A website where people can rant into the void of the internet.
Developer: Daniel Cender
Customer
There is no traditional customer to this site. Rather it will be an open
source model that can be adapted for other websites.
The author will maintain a live version of the site model for people to
experience anonymously.
Other organizations may desire to use this model to build their own
live website feed.
Developers may use this model to experiment and build on to create
a augmented clone of Reddit, 4chan, or Twitter sites.
Editing and Access Permissions
The site developers, code reviewers, or graphic artists would be
allowed to augment this site.
As this will be a site built by one developer, only the site author will
have access to edit the codebase.
Objectives
Provide an online environment that allows consumers to easily share
their thoughts and questions to a public space.
Provides absolute anonymity to the posters who choose to remain
anonymous
Competition
https://www.quora.com
https://www.reddit.com
Competition (cont.)
https://www.tumblr.com/
